Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

Concept:     Word Embeddings
Category:    Representation
Definition:  Dense vectors where semantic similarity = vector proximity
Year:        2013
Researchers: Mikolov et al.
Applications:NLP, recommendation, search
Related:     Word2Vec, GloVe, BERT embeddings

Concept:     RAG
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Combines retrieval from knowledge base with generative model
Year:        2020
Researchers: Lewis et al.
Applications:QA, chatbots, enterprise AI
Related:     Vector database, semantic search, LLM

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

