============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is relativity?
A1: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q2: What is gravity?
A2: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q3: What is a neuron?
A3: A neuron is a nerve cell that processes and transmits
     information through electrical and chemical signals.
     Key parts: dendrites (receive signals), cell body, axon
     (send signals).

Q4: What is metabolism?
A4: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q5: What is the periodic table?
A5: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

